comments: Olynyk (UTA) and Kuminga (GSW) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Kuminga (GSW) is moving alongside Olynyk's (UTA) path and he maintains a legal guarding position during the drive.

Olynyk (UTA) gathers the ball and lands on both feel. He moves his right foot, which establishes his left as his pivot. After pivoting, he steps forward with his left (pivot) foot before taking his shot.
Kuminga (GSW) legally contests Olynyk's (UTA) shot attempt.
Poole (GSW) does not put part of his hand under the ball, and either carry it from one point to another or bring it to a pause and then continue to dribble again.
Alexander-Walker (UTA) is moving alongside Poole's (GSW) path and legally contests his driving shot attempt.
Looney (GSW) and Kessler (UTA) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Poole (GSW) and Clarkson (UTA) go for the loose ball.
Clarkson (UTA) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Kuminga (GSW) and Clarkson (UTA) engage and disengage.
Clarkson (UTA) brushes Thompson's (GSW) arm before he starts his upward shooting motion.
Kuminga (GSW) establishes a wide screening position in Alexander-Walker's (UTA) path and contact occurs to his leg.
Kuminga (GSW) and Kessler (UTA) raise their hands in pursuit of the loose ball and incidental contact occurs during rebounding.
Kessler (UTA) and Kuminga (GSW) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Beasley (UTA) and Looney (GSW) engage and disengage during the rebound attempt.
Kessler (UTA) cleanly blocks Looney's (GSW) shot attempt near the rim.
Kuminga (GSW) and Alexander-Walker (UTA) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as Alexander-Walker secures the loose ball.
Olynyk (UTA) establishes himself in Kuminga's (GSW) path and does not deliver contact.
Moody (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position on Clarkson's (UTA) drive.
Clarkson's (UTA) momentum carries him into Looney (GSW), who is in a legal vertical position.
Olynyk (UTA) maintains a legal forearm to Poole's (GSW) side during his drive and does not extend. Poole stumbles on his own accord.
The timeout called by the Jazz is recognized before Poole (GSW) makes contact to Olynyk (UTA) while he is out of bounds.
Moody (GSW) commits a take foul on Alexander-Walker (UTA).
Kuminga (GSW) and Olynyk (UTA) briefly engage and disengage as the pick is set.
Kuminga (GSW) turns slightly towards Alexander-Walker (UTA) and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Kuminga (GSW) moves along Clarkson's (UTA) path as Clarkson turns toward the rim.
Kuminga (GSW) cleanly blocks Clarkson's (UTA) driving shot attempt, and the arm contact after the legal block is incidental.
The crew communicated with the Replay Center and determined that the foul called on Clarkson (UTA) met the criteria for a flagrant foul penalty 2.
During their review, the crew determined that a double technical foul was warranted on Kuminga (GSW) and Beasley (UTA).
During their review, the crew determined that a double technical foul was warranted on Kuminga (GSW) and Beasley (UTA).
Olynyk (UTA) extends his arm as Thompson (GSW) turns away with the ball. The contact is marginal.
Olynyk (UTA) cleanly connects with and then dislodges the ball from Thompson (GSW).
Thompson (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball as he contests Fontecchio's (UTA) jump shot attempt, and the contact to his off hand after the legal block is incidental.

After gathering the ball, Poole (GSW) brings his arms up as Olynyk (UTA) steps forward toward him, and contact occurs to Olynyk's face. Poole is entitled to his vertical space (even though he is not shooting) and since he did not extend his arms forward into Olynyk or appear to seek out contact, the contact is deemed to have occurred because Olynyk is moving forward towards Poole's space. Given the fact that Poole is not in a shooting motion, a no call is appropriate. If a foul were warranted, it would be on Olynyk.
Fontecchio (UTA) makes contact with Poole's (GSW) hip and back as he makes contact with the ball.
Alexander-Walker (UTA) cleanly dislodges the ball from Poole (GSW).  Any ensuing hand/arm contact is considered incidental.
After the ball becomes loose, Poole (GSW) and Olynyk (UTA) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs.
Moody (GSW) legally contests Fontecchio's (UTA) layup attempt.
Alexander-Walker (UTA) cleanly deflects the ball away from Moody (GSW).
